@startuml Admin_Workflow
!theme plain
title Iels - Admin System Management & Oversight Workflow

skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #7B1FA2
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #4A148C
skinparam ActivityFontColor #FFFFFF
skinparam DecisionBackgroundColor #9C27B0
skinparam DecisionBorderColor #4A148C
skinparam DecisionFontColor #FFFFFF

participant Admin
participant "AdminDashboard\n(UI)" as Dashboard
participant "UserService\n(Business Logic)" as US
participant "CourseService" as CS
participant "SQLite/Supabase\n(Database)" as DB
participant "SessionManager\n(Auth)" as Session
participant "EmailService" as Email

activate Dashboard

Dashboard -> Session: 1. Retrieve current admin
activate Session
Session -->> Dashboard: Return Admin object
deactivate Session

Dashboard -> US: 2. getSystemStatistics()
activate US
US -> DB: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Users
activate DB
DB -->> US: Return user count (e.g., 1,245)
deactivate DB

US -> DB: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Courses WHERE status = 'ACTIVE'
activate DB
DB -->> US: Return active courses (e.g., 86)
deactivate DB

US -> DB: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Enrollments
activate DB
DB -->> US: Return total enrollments (e.g., 3,421)
deactivate DB

US -> Dashboard: Display dashboard statistics\n[Users, Courses, Enrollments, Revenue]
deactivate US

Dashboard -> Dashboard: 3. Display AdminDashboard\n- System Statistics Cards\n- Menu: User Management | Course Approvals\n       | System Reports | Settings\n- Analytics Charts (role distribution, activity)

loop Admin Activities
    Admin -> Dashboard: 4. Choose admin action
    
    alt 👥 User Management
        Dashboard -> US: 5. getAllUsers(filters)
        activate US
        US -> DB: SELECT id, name, nim, email, role, status, created_at\nFROM Users ORDER BY created_at DESC\nLIMIT 50 OFFSET 0
        activate DB
        DB -->> US: Return paginated user list
        deactivate DB
        
        US -> Dashboard: Display user management table\n[Name, NIM, Email, Role, Status, Actions]
        deactivate US
        
        loop User Admin Loop
            Admin -> Dashboard: 6. Click on user row
            
            alt View Profile
                Dashboard -> US: 7. getUserDetails(userId)
                activate US
                US -> DB: SELECT * FROM Users WHERE id = ?
                activate DB
                DB -->> US: Return full user object
                deactivate DB
                
                US -> DB: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM Enrollments\nWHERE user_id = ?
                activate DB
                DB -->> US: Return enrollment count
                deactivate DB
                
                US -> Dashboard: Display user profile\n[Personal info, enrollment history, role]
                deactivate US
                
            else (2) Change Status (Activate/Deactivate)
                Admin -> Dashboard: 8. Click status toggle\n(active ↔ inactive)
                
                Dashboard -> US: 9. updateUserStatus(userId, status)
                activate US
                
                US -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
                activate DB
                
                alt Set to ACTIVE
                    US -> DB: UPDATE Users SET status = 'ACTIVE'\nWHERE id = ?
                    
                else Set to INACTIVE
                    US -> DB: UPDATE Users SET status = 'INACTIVE'\nWHERE id = ?
                    
                    US -> DB: DELETE FROM Sessions\nWHERE user_id = ? AND active = TRUE
                end
                
                DB -->> US: Return success
                DB -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
                deactivate DB
                
                US -> Email: 9b. sendStatusNotification(user.email, status)
                activate Email
                Email -> Email: Compose email\n[Status changed notification]
                Email -> Email: Queue for sending
                deactivate Email
                
                Dashboard -> Admin: ✅ Status updated\n[User notified]
                deactivate US
                
            else (3) Reset Password
                Admin -> Dashboard: 10. Click "Reset Password"\nbutton
                
                Dashboard -> US: 11. generateTemporaryPassword()
                activate US
                US -> US: Generate 12-char random password
                US -> US: Hash with BCrypt (cost ≥ 12)
                
                US -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
                activate DB
                US -> DB: UPDATE Users SET\npassword_hash = ?,\ntemp_password_set = TRUE,\nlast_password_reset = NOW()\nWHERE id = ?
                
                DB -->> US: Return success
                DB -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
                deactivate DB
                
                US -> Email: 11b. sendPasswordReset(user.email, tempPassword)
                activate Email
                Email -> Email: Compose email\n[Subject: "Password Reset"]\n[Body: temp password + instructions]
                Email -> Email: Send immediately
                deactivate Email
                
                Dashboard -> Admin: ✅ Password reset sent\n[User must change on next login]
                deactivate US
                
            else (4) Delete User
                Admin -> Dashboard: 12. Click "Delete Account"
                
                Dashboard -> Dashboard: Show confirmation dialog\n[Warning: Action is permanent!]
                
                Admin -> Dashboard: 13. Confirm deletion
                
                Dashboard -> US: 14. deleteUser(userId)
                activate US
                
                US -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
                activate DB
                
                alt Has no active enrollments
                    US -> DB: DELETE FROM UserPreferences WHERE user_id = ?
                    US -> DB: DELETE FROM Submissions WHERE user_id = ?
                    US -> DB: DELETE FROM Enrollments WHERE user_id = ?
                    US -> DB: DELETE FROM Users WHERE id = ?
                    
                    DB -->> US: Return success
                else Has active enrollments
                    DB -->> US: Error\n"User has active enrollments"
                    US -->> Dashboard: Show error\n"Cannot delete: has enrollments"
                end
                
                DB -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
                deactivate DB
                
                Dashboard -> Admin: ✅ User deleted
                deactivate US
                
            else (5) Assign/Change Role
                Admin -> Dashboard: 15. Click "Change Role"
                
                Dashboard -> Dashboard: Display role selector\n[STUDENT | INSTRUCTOR | ADMIN]
                
                Admin -> Dashboard: 16. Select new role
                
                Dashboard -> US: 17. updateUserRole(userId, newRole)
                activate US
                
                US -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
                activate DB
                US -> DB: UPDATE Users SET role = ?\nWHERE id = ?
                
                DB -->> US: Return success
                DB -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
                deactivate DB
                
                US -> Email: 17b. sendRoleChangeNotification()
                activate Email
                Email -> Email: Notify user of role change
                deactivate Email
                
                Dashboard -> Admin: ✅ Role updated
                deactivate US
            end
        end
        
    else (2) 📋 Course Approvals
        Dashboard -> CS: 18. getPendingCourses()
        activate CS
        
        CS -> DB: SELECT * FROM Courses\nWHERE status = 'PENDING'\nORDER BY created_at ASC
        activate DB
        DB -->> CS: Return pending course list
        deactivate DB
        
        CS -> Dashboard: Display approval queue\n[Course name, instructor, date submitted]
        deactivate CS
        
        loop Approval Loop
            Admin -> Dashboard: 19. Click on pending course
            
            Dashboard -> CS: 20. getCourseForApproval(courseId)
            activate CS
            CS -> DB: SELECT * FROM Courses WHERE id = ?
            activate DB
            DB -->> CS: Return course details
            deactivate DB
            
            CS -> DB: SELECT * FROM Users WHERE id = Courses.instructor_id
            activate DB
            DB -->> CS: Return instructor info
            deactivate DB
            
            CS -> Dashboard: Display review screen\n[Course info, syllabus, instructor credentials]
            deactivate CS
            
            Admin -> Dashboard: 21. Review course details\n[Check: requirements met, content quality]
            
            Admin -> Dashboard: 22. Choose decision
            
            if Approve Course ✅
                Dashboard -> CS: 23. approveCourse(courseId)
                activate CS
                
                CS -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
                activate DB
                CS -> DB: UPDATE Courses SET status = 'ACTIVE'\nWHERE id = ?
                
                DB -->> CS: Return success
                DB -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
                deactivate DB
                
                CS -> Email: 23b. notifyInstructor(instructor_email)\n[Approval notification]
                activate Email
                Email -> Email: Send approval email
                deactivate Email
                
                Dashboard -> Dashboard: Remove from approval queue
                Dashboard -> Admin: ✅ Course approved\n[Available to students]
                deactivate CS
                
            else Reject Course ❌
                Dashboard -> Dashboard: Show rejection reason input
                Admin -> Dashboard: 24. Enter rejection reason
                
                Dashboard -> CS: 25. rejectCourse(courseId, reason)
                activate CS
                
                CS -> DB: BEGIN TRANSACTION
                activate DB
                CS -> DB: UPDATE Courses SET status = 'REJECTED',\nrejection_reason = ?\nWHERE id = ?
                
                DB -->> CS: Return success
                DB -> DB: COMMIT TRANSACTION
                deactivate DB
                
                CS -> Email: 25b. notifyInstructor(instructor_email)\n[Rejection with reason]
                activate Email
                Email -> Email: Send rejection email\nwith improvement suggestions
                deactivate Email
                
                Dashboard -> Dashboard: Status: REJECTED\n[Instructor can resubmit]
                Dashboard -> Admin: ✅ Course rejected
                deactivate CS
                
            else Review Later 📌
                Dashboard -> Admin: Status remains PENDING\n[Will appear in queue later]
            end
        end
        
    else (3) 📊 System Reports
        Admin -> Dashboard: 26. Click "Reports"
        
        Dashboard -> US: 27. generateSystemReport(dateRange)
        activate US
        
        US -> DB: SELECT * FROM Users\nJOIN (enrollment stats)
        activate DB
        DB -->> US: Return report data
        deactivate DB
        
        US -> Dashboard: Generate charts\n[User growth, enrollment trends, revenue]
        deactivate US
        
        Admin -> Dashboard: 28. View analytics dashboards\n[Filter by date, role, course, etc.]
        
        Admin -> Dashboard: 29. Export report\n(CSV, PDF, Excel)
        
    else (4) ⚙️ System Settings
        Admin -> Dashboard: 30. Click "Settings"
        
        Dashboard -> Dashboard: Display configuration options\n[Database settings, email config]\n[Supabase API keys, user limits]
        
        Admin -> Dashboard: 31. Update settings
        
        Dashboard -> Dashboard: Validate new configuration\n[Test database connection]\n[Verify API endpoints]
        
        Dashboard -> Dashboard: 32. Save configuration\n[Update .env or config file]
        
        Dashboard -> Admin: ✅ Settings updated\n[Some require restart]
        
    else (5) 🔍 System Audit Log
        Admin -> Dashboard: 33. Click "Audit Log"
        
        Dashboard -> US: 34. getAuditLog(filters)
        activate US
        
        US -> DB: SELECT timestamp, user_id, action, resource,\nold_value, new_value FROM AuditLog\nORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 100
        activate DB
        DB -->> US: Return audit records
        deactivate DB
        
        US -> Dashboard: Display table\n[User, Timestamp, Action, Resource, Changes]
        deactivate US
        
        Admin -> Dashboard: Review system activity\n[Search, filter, export]
    end
end

Dashboard -> Dashboard: 35. All admin changes logged to AuditLog

deactivate Dashboard

note right of Admin, Dashboard
    **Admin Responsibilities:**
    1. User Lifecycle: Create, read, update, delete users
    2. Role Management: Assign roles and permissions
    3. Course Oversight: Approve courses before launch
    4. Quality Control: Monitor system health & performance
    5. Compliance: Audit logging, data retention
    
    **Database Operations:**
    - Users table: Full access (all roles)
    - Courses: Status workflow (PENDING → ACTIVE/REJECTED)
    - AuditLog: All changes tracked with timestamp + user
    - Email notifications: Sent to affected users
    
    **Security & Access Control:**
    - Admin role has highest privileges
    - All admin actions logged to AuditLog
    - Sensitive operations require confirmation
    - IP/device audit optional
    - Session timeout after 30 min inactivity
    
    **Error Handling:**
    - Prevent cascade deletes of active enrollments
    - Notify users of critical changes
    - Log all failures to error tracking
    - Alert on suspicious activity patterns
end note

@enduml
